The paper proposes a new loss function for learning deep embeddings, which is a common task in machine learning and computer vision. The use of histograms and soft assignment operations suggests a focus on data representation and feature extraction, which are key topics in the subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions applications to natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM), indicating a potential interest in cross-disciplinary research. Finally, the use of stochastic optimization and comparison to recently proposed alternatives suggests a focus on practical implementation and empirical evaluation, which are common themes in the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
